    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This episode includes five sections: a feature report on a labor strike, street interviews, a cultural program, an interview with Chinese playwright Cao Yu (曹禺), and a 13-minute Hong Kong documentary. The first part features a labor strike outside Silver Palace Restaurant in Chinatown. An unequal allocation of tips is the main issue. In the second part, hosts interview Chinatown residents about their views on the Silver Palace Restaurant labor strike. The third part features a special program called Asian American Experience, in which Asian-American young people are preparing for the American Heritage Week exhibition. The fourth section covers interviews with Chinese playwright Cao Yu. The fifth section of the episode shows documentary Old Man and His Painting (丁公的畫) (1977), in which Chinese painter Ting Yin Yung (丁衍庸)'s life in Hong Kong is documented.</field>
